-Year%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2F15-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E15-year%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20in%20the%20mid-5%25%20range%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow%20data.%20In%20September%2C%2015-year%20rates%20averaged%205.01%25%2C%20but%20they've%20been%20trending%20higher%20so%20far%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20the%20predictability%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20fixed%20rate%20but%20are%20looking%20to%20spend%20less%20on%20interest%20over%20the%20life%20of%20your%20loan%2C%20a%2015-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20might%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20you.%20Because%20these%20terms%20are%20shorter%20and%20have%20lower%20rates%20than%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20you%20could%20potentially%20save%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20interest.%20However%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20monthly%20payment%20than%20you%20would%20with%20a%20longer%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Refinance%20Rates%5C%22%3ECurrent%20Mortgage%20Refinance%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20dropping%20last%20month%2C%20refinance%20rates%20have%20been%20a%20bit%20higher%20so%20far%20in%20October.%20In%20September%2C%2030-year%20refinance%20rates%20averaged%205.89%25%2C%20while%2015-year%20refinance%20rates%20were%20around%205.19%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20Much%20Do%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Need%20to%20Drop%20to%20Refinance%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20wondering%20if%20you%20should%20refinance%20now%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20crunch%20the%20numbers%20to%20see%20if%20it%20makes%20sense.%20Some%20experts%20advise%20only%20refinancing%20if%20you%20can%20reduce%20your%20rate%20by%20a%20percentage%20point%20or%20more%2C%20but%20it%20really%20comes%20down%20to%20whether%20it%20works%20for%20your%20individual%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20can%20save%20enough%20each%20month%20by%20refinancing%20that%20you%20can%20recoup%20your%20costs%20in%20a%20reasonable%20amount%20of%20time%2C%20it%20might%20be%20worth%20it.%20You%20can%20calculate%20this%20by%20dividing%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhat-are-mortgage-closing-costs%5C%22%3Eclosing%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20amount%20you're%20saving%20on%20your%20monthly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Faverage-mortgage-payment%5C%22%3Emortgage%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%2C%20if%20you%20paid%20%243%2C000%20to%20refinance%20and%20were%20able%20to%20lower%20your%20monthly%20payment%20by%20%24200%2C%20it%20would%20take%20you%2015%20months%20to%20break%20even%20on%20your%20refinance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Rate%20Trends%5C%22%3E5-Year%20Mortgage%20Rate%20Trends%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%2030-year%20and%2015-year%20mortgage%20rates%20have%20trended%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20according%20to%20Freddie%20Mac%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FdBxcL%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Weekly%20mortgage%20rates%20over%20the%20last%205%20years%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22503%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20Factors%20Influence%20Mortgage%20Rates%3F%5C%22%3EWhat%20Factors%20Influence%20Mortgage%20Rates%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-are-mortgage-rates-determined%5C%22%3EMortgage%20rates%20are%20determined%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20variety%20of%20different%20factors%2C%20including%20larger%20economic%20trends%2C%20Federal%20Reserve%20policy%2C%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fstate-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3Estate's%20current%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20type%20of%20loan%20you're%20getting%2C%20a