ober.%20Rates%20trended%20down%20as%20the%20economy%20cooled%20and%20the%20Fed%20geared%20up%20to%20start%20cutting%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate.%20Now%20that%20the%20Fed%20has%20cut%20rates%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20may%20not%20drop%20much%20in%20October.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20incoming%20data%20suggests%20that%20the%20economy%20is%20weakening%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20could%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20Low%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20are%20unlikely%20to%20drop%20back%20down%20to%20the%20historic%20lows%20of%202020%20and%202021%2C%20when%2030-year%20fixed%20rates%20fell%20below%203%25.%20But%20rates%20are%20expected%20to%20continue%20to%20ease%20throughout%20the%20next%20year%20or%20two%2C%20and%20it's%20possible%20rates%20could%20ultimately%20settle%20in%20closer%20to%205%25%20in%20a%20few%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWill%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%20Down%20in%202025%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20major%20forecasts%20expect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwill-mortgage-rates-go-down-this-year%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%20to%20go%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20throughout%202025%20as%20the%20Fed%20continues%20to%20lower%20its%20benchmark%20rate.%20But%20because%20mortgage%20rates%20are%20influenced%20by%20the%20economy%2C%20this%20forecast%20could%20change%20depending%20on%20how%20the%20economy%20evolves%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftodays-mortgage-rates-friday-18-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729245604000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F626ff39686fa90001905fbcc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftodays-mortgage-rates-friday-18-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22These%20are%20today's%20mortgage%20and%20refinance%20rates.%20Mortgage%20rates%20are%20down%20slightly%20this%20week%20but%20remain%20elevated%20compared%20to%20where%20they%20were%20last%20month.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Molly%20Grace)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftodays-mortgage-rates-friday-18-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Here's%20what%20Wall%20Street%20money%20managers%20are%20doing%20to%20prepare%20their%20portfolios%20for%20their%203%20biggest%20election%20concerns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221580%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20split%20image%20of%20Kamala%20Harris%20and%20Donald%20Trump%20speaking%20at%20rallies.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b90446b4912df3ae1a9c26%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKamala%20Harris%20and%20Donald%20Trump.%3Cp%3ERONDA%20CHURCHILL%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images.%20NATALIE%20BEHRING%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20election%20day%20draws%20near%2C%20400%20Wall%20Street%20money%20managers%20identified%20their%20top%20concerns.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENational%20debt%2C%20economic%20growth%2C%20and%20immigration%20reform%20are%20big%20issues%20for%20the%20next%20administration.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20institutional%20investors%20are%20preparing%20their%20portfolios%20and%20hedging%20risk.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20just%20a%20few%20weeks%20until%20Election%20Day%2C%20the%20presidential%20race%20is%20neck%20and%20neck%20between%20Kamala%20Harris%20and%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20at%20stake%20in%20November.%20Policy%20initiatives%20could%20have%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20especially%20on%20issues%20concerning%20inflation%2C%20the%20housing%20market%2C%20employment%2C%20and%20international%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%241.3%20trillion%20asset%20manager%20PGIM%20surveyed%20400%20institutional%20investors%20collectively%20overseeing%20%249%20trillion%20in%20assets%20under%20management%20about%20the%20election.%20Most%20investors%20surveyed%20agreed%20that%20elections%20influenced%20how%20they%20allocated%20funds%20in%20their%20portfolios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%2046%25%20of%20the%20investors%20surveyed%20said%20that%20a%20Republican%20sweep%20across%20the%20White%20House%20and%20Congress%20would%20be%20the%20optimal%20outcome%20for%20the%20market.%2029%25%20of%20investors%20preferred%20split%20control%20of%20the%20White%20House%20and%20Congress.%20Investors%20can%20benefit%20from%20both%20parties%3A%20Republicans%20would%20likely%20pass%20investor-friendly%20tax%20and%20energy%20policy%2C%20while%20Democrats%20would%20pass%20more%20favorable%20US-China%20and%20trade%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20Wall%20Street%20is%20worried%20about%20this%20election%20cycle%20and%20how%20top%20money%20managers%20are%20preparing%20their%20portfolios%20for%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c2ba8bee-0e1c-46d1-9407-b7e2f9e02c0b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWall%20Street's%203%20biggest%20election%20concerns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20one%20clear%20standout%20issue%3A%20the%20%3Cstrong%3Enational%20debt%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%2035%25%20of%20institutional%20managers%20flagged%20the%20US%20national%20debt%20as%20the%20most%20important%20policy%20change%20they%20wanted%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKara%20Murphy%2C%20chief%20investment%20officer%20at%20Kestra%20Investment%20Management%2C%20says%20the%20deficit%20will%20continue%20to%20balloon%20from%20its%20current%20level%20of%20%2435%20trillion%20as%20higher%20Medicare%2C%20Social%20Security%2C%20and%20interest%20expenses%20stack%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20neither%20candidate%20has%20put%20forward%20a%20concrete%20plan%20to%20address%20this%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20candidates'%20relative%20silence%20on%20the%20deficit%20shows%20that%20it's%20an%20American%20problem%20%E2%80%93%20not%20just%20a%20party%20problem%20%E2%80%93%20and%20one%20so%20big%20and%20intractable%20that%20the%20next%20president%20isn't%20likely%20to%20be%20able%20to%20make%20much%20of%20a%20near-term%20impact%2C%26quot%3B%20Murphy%20wrote%20in%20a%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeventeen%20percent%20of%20investors%20responded%20that%20%3Cstrong%3Efueling%20economic%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20was%20their%20biggest%20concern.%20There%20are%20both%20domestic%20and%20international%20challenges%20to%20the%20health%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20with%20institutional%20managers%20flagging%20issues%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-odds-rising-inflation-geopolitcal-concerns-surge-investing-strategy-volatility-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einflation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks-hedge-geopolitical-china-risk-retaining-upside-international-beijing-stimulus-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS-China%20relations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20likely%20that%20the%20next%20administration%20will%20implement%20new%20tariffs%2C%20regardless%20of%20which%20party%20takes%20the%20White%20House%2C%20according%20to%20PGIM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Trump%20is%20well-known%20for%20his%20love%20of%20tariffs%2C%20Harris%20isn't%20exactly%20anti-tariff%20either.%20Murphy%20points%20out%20the%20Biden-Harris%20administration%20has%20kept%20many%20of%20the%20tariffs%20that%20Trump%20passed%20during%20his%20presidency%2C%20and%20even%20enacted%20additional%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreased%20trade%20tensions%20could%20have%20negative%20implications%20for%20both%20US%20and%20international%20markets%20in%20China%2C%20Latin%20America%2C%20and%20Southeast%20Asia.%20Tariffs%20often%20have%20inflationary%20effects%20by%20slowing%20down%20trade%20and%20raising%20prices%20for%20consumers.%20The%20results%20of%20the%20presidential%20election%20will%20clarify%20how%20many%20new%20tariffs%20to%20expect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20biggest%20concern%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimmigration-policy-boost-labor-market-national-debt-job-market-taxes-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Eimmigration%20reform%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%2015%25%20of%20investors%20placing%20it%20as%20their%20most%20important%20policy%20concern.%20Investment%20advisor%20Research%20Affiliates%20sees%20an%20urgent%20need%20for%20immigration%20reform%20as%20the%20US%20population%20growth%20rate%20continues%20to%20decline%2C%20harming%20the%20labor%20market.%20According%20to%20Research%20Affiliates%2C%20policies%20such%20as%20removing%20the%20cap%20on%20green%20cards%20for%20immigrants%20with%20higher%20education%20degrees%20in%20STEM%20fields%20could%20solve%20this%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2296c99c05-0f43-49e9-bcc5-3b7a39e8f265%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPreparing%20your%20portfolio%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tight%20race%20makes%20it%20unlikely%20for%20a%20single%20party%20to%20hold%20a%20sweeping%20majority%20in%20the%20House%20and%20Senate%20and%20pass%20drastic%20policy%20changes.%20However%2C%20the%20election%20winner%20still%20has%20implications%20for%20portfolios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20survey%20respondent%2C%20a%20portfolio%20manager%20for%20a%20US-based%20pension%20fund%2C%20said%20elections%20have%20%26quot%3Bbeen%20a%20big%20factor%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20allocating%20money.%20A%20Republican%20president%20is%20likely%20to%20benefit%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industries%2C%20while%20a%20Democrat%20win%20will%20boost%20healthcare%2C%20the%20portfolio%20manager%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20investment%20director%20for%20another%20pension%20fund%20shared%20the%20following%20investment%20outlook%20regarding%20the%20ongoing%20decline%20in%20globalization%20and%20trade%20relations%3A%20%26quot%3BGiven%20reshoring%2C%20friend-