rbital%20Test%20Vehicle%20(OTV-7)%2C%20is%20an%20experimental%20space%20plane%20operated%20by%20the%20United%20States%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2C%20noindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spaceforce.mil%2FNews%2FArticle-Display%2FArticle%2F3932137%2Fx-37b-begins-novel-space-maneuver%2F%5C%22%3ESpace%20Force%20%3C%2Fa%3E(USSF).%20While%20the%20full%20scope%20of%20its%20mission%20remains%20classified%2C%20the%20X-37B%20has%20garnered%20significant%20attention%20for%20its%20cutting-edge%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20release%2C%20the%20US%20Space%20Force%20said%20that%20the%20X-37B%20Orbital%20Test%20Vehicle%20(OTV-7)%20is%20set%20to%20carry%20aerobraking%2C%20which%20will%20allow%20it%20to%20adjust%20its%20orbit%20around%20Earth%20and%20safely%20discard%20its%20service%20module%20in%20line%20with%20international%20guidelines%20for%20managing%20space%20debris.%20Since%20December%2028%2C%202023%2C%20the%20US%20Space%20Force%2C%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20Air%20Force%20Rapid%20Capabilities%20Office%2C%20has%20been%20conducting%20radiation%20impact%20studies%20and%20trialling%20Space%20Domain%20Awareness%20technologies%20while%20in%20a%20highly%20elliptical%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAerobraking%20involves%20the%20spacecraft%20making%20multiple%20passes%20through%20Earth's%20atmosphere%2C%20using%20the%20atmospheric%20drag%20to%20alter%20its%20orbit%20while%20conserving%20fuel.%20Once%20this%20manoeuvre%20is%20successfully%20completed%2C%20the%20X-37B%20will%20continue%20its%20testing%20and%20experimental%20missions.%20After%20fulfilling%20its%20objectives%2C%20the%20vehicle%20will%20de-orbit%20and%20return%20to%20Earth%20safely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrank%20Kendall%2C%20Secretary%20of%20the%20Air%20Force%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20novel%20and%20efficient%20series%20of%20manoeuvres%20demonstrates%20the%20Space%20Force's%20commitment%20to%20achieving%20groundbreaking%20innovation%20as%20it%20conducts%20national%20security%20missions%20in%20space.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20marks%20the%20first%20time%20the%20US%20Space%20Force%20and%20the%20X-37B%20will%20attempt%20the%20dynamic%20aerobraking%20manoeuvre%2C%20building%20on%20the%20success%20of%20six%20previous%20missions%20where%20the%20space%20plane%20has%20operated%20safely%2C%20according%20to%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20official%20illustration%20of%20the%20spacecraft%20unveiled%20last%20year%20hinted%20at%20its%20potential%2C%20depicting%20the%20futuristic%20vehicle%20intercepting%20a%20hostile%20satellite%20attempting%20to%20disable%20a%20friendly%20satellite%2C%20suggesting%20its%20role%20in%20space%20defence%20operations%2C%20stated%20a%20report%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2C%20noindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2024%2F10%2F15%2Fscience%2Fsecretive-us-spaceship-to-attempt-unprecedented-maneuvers-above-earth%2F%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAnother%20report%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2C%20noindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Ftechnology%2Fengineering%2Ftop-secret-x-37b-space-plane-will-execute-never-before-seen-maneuvers-on-its-descent-to-earth%5C%22%3ELive%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E%20stated%20that%20X-37B%2C%20a%20covert%2C%20remotely%20operated%20spacecraft%20developed%20by%20Boeing%2C%20is%20designed%20for%20undisclosed%20missions%20under%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20(DOD).%20While%20its%20specific%20operations%20remain%20classified%2C%20Live%20Science%20said%20that%20the%20spacecraft%20has%20previously%20been%20used%20to%20study%20the%20impact%20of%20solar%20radiation%20on%20seeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729242600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fkcee55jg_spacecraft_625x300_15_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-aerobraking-that-a-secretive-us-spacecraft-will-perform-in-earths-orbit-6816189%