E2%80%9D%20she%20laments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20MRI%20confirmed%20Sneha%E2%80%99s%20suspicions%20%E2%80%94%20she%20had%20endometriosis.%20%E2%80%9CI%20cried%20that%20day.%20I%20felt%20robbed%20of%20so%20many%20life%20experiences.%20I%20wish%20they%20had%20just%20listened%20to%20me%20when%20I%20told%20them%20that%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20normal%20period%20pain%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202021%2C%20she%20underwent%20surgery%20to%20check%20her%20endometrial%20tissue.%20The%20doctor%20put%20her%20on%20a%20hormone%20treatment%3B%20this%20didn%E2%80%99t%20work%20for%20her%2C%20leading%20to%20further%20anxiety.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20closed%20me%20up%20and%20said%20that%20the%20tissue%20didn%E2%80%99t%20warrant%20so%20much%20pain.%20It%20messed%20with%20my%20emotional%20and%20mental%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sneha%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnhappy%20with%20the%20treatment%20and%20now%20aware%20and%20educated%20about%20the%20condition%2C%20she%20found%20an%20endometriosis%20expert%20in%20Mumbai.%20Another%20MRI%20scan%20revealed%20that%20she%20had%20a%20cyst%20that%20was%20pressing%20down%20on%20the%20ligament%20behind%20the%20uterus%2C%20which%20possibly%20led%20to%20her%20pain.%20So%20in%20December%202022%2C%20she%20underwent%20another%20surgery%20where%20these%20cysts%20were%20taken%20out.%20A%20histopathology%20report%20also%20confirmed%20that%20she%20had%20endometriosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20procedure%2C%20life%20has%20been%20much%20better%20for%20Sneha.%20She%20no%20longer%20has%20to%20pop%20painkillers%20and%20is%20able%20to%20lead%20a%20normal%20life.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20a%20lot%20of%20gaslighting%20and%20insinuating%20that%20I%20was%20clamouring%20for%20attention%2C%20this%20diagnosis%20gave%20me%20the%20validation%20I%20needed.%20I%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20wrong%3B%20I%20kn